             sworn.</p>
               <p>I am <rs id="t17810425-54-viclabel263" type="occupation">book-keeper</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17810425-54-victim537 t17810425-54-viclabel263"></join> to the Bell inn, in Warwick-lane. On Friday morning, the 6th of April, between three and four o'clock, I was unloading the waggon at the corner of <placeName id="t17810425-54-crimeloc264">Hart-street, Warwick-lane, Newgate-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17810425-54-crimeloc264" type="placeName" value="Hart-street, Warwick-lane, Newgate-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17810425-54-crimeloc264" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17810425-54-off261 t17810425-54-crimeloc264"></join>: I had put fifteen flats of butter, and three flats of eggs, at the corner of the street, as I usually do; I had a flat of meat I was going to carry to one of the salesmen; the things till delivered are in my care, and I am answerable for them: as I was going round one corner of the street, I saw the prisoner come running round the other out of the market; I had some suspicion, and ran after him; I was within about ten yards of him, and saw him take a flat, the top flat; he ran away with it immediately; I ran after him, and overtook him; I caught him by the collar; upon that he dropped the flat: I saw it opened afterwards; it contained 150 eggs.</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>I was going to market; a man asked me to earn a groat by carrying this flat to the Mansion-house: as soon as Davis laid hold of me, the man that put it on my back ran away.</p>
               <p>To Davis. Had the waggoner any directions to send away any things in your absence? - No; I always do it.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17810425-54-verdict265" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17810425-54-verdict265" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>Tried by the First London Jury, before Mr. RECORDER.</p>
